Falun Dafa practitioners participated in the 100th New York City Veterans Day Parade for the 16th consecutive year, showing their support for the United States veterans.

President Donald Trump started the event by speaking at the opening ceremony at Madison Square Park on November 11, 2019. Over 25,000 paraders and 300 marching units participated in the parade. There were 150 vehicles and 30 floats. It began on Fifth Avenue at 23rd Street and continued north to 56th Street. The paraders were warmly received by the thousands of spectators.
